# Project rules for AI agents

## Code style

- TypeScript: stay strict; avoid `any` unless there is a clear, narrow reason.
- React: functional components and hooks; keep state and effects easy to follow.
- Names and functions: descriptive, small, single-purpose.

## Stack & tooling

- **React 19** + **TypeScript** + **Vite 8** (`@vitejs/plugin-react`), ESLint flat config (`eslint.config.js`).
- After substantive changes, run **`npm run lint`** and **`npm run build`**; fix anything introduced by the edit.
- Scripts: `npm run dev`, `npm run build`, `npm run preview`, `npm run lint`.

## Product context â€” simple-name-picker

- Small front-end app for **choosing or drawing names** fairly from a list (flows will evolve under `src/`).
- Prefer **simple, accessible UI** (keyboard, labels, readable contrast) as features are added.
- **Persistence** (e.g. `localStorage`) is optional until the app defines it; do not assume files or hooks from other repos exist here.

## Editing habits

- Prefer changing existing files over adding new ones when it keeps the design clear.
- Match indentation and formatting already in the file.
- Do not add dependencies without a short justification; keep the repo lightweight unless product needs say otherwise.

## Project structure (evolve as needed)

- Today: `src/App.tsx`, `src/main.tsx`, styles under `src/`, assets in `src/assets` and `public/`.
- As it grows: `src/components/`, `src/hooks/`, `src/types/` when duplication or clarity calls for it.

No rigid per-component `index.tsx` + `types.ts` + `styles.css` layout unless this codebase adopts that pattern.

## Commit messages

Use [Conventional Commits](https://www.conventionalcommits.org/en/v1.0.0/):

`type[optional scope]: description`

- **feat:** â€” new feature (MINOR)
- **fix:** â€” bug fix (PATCH)
- **docs:** / **style:** / **refactor:** / **perf:** / **test:** / **chore:** â€” as usual
- **BREAKING CHANGE:** `!` after type/scope or footer for MAJOR

Example: `feat: add name list editor`

## Versioning & changelog (when releasing)

- **SemVer** in `package.json` when cutting releases.
- **Changelog:** optional at `0.0.0`; if you maintain one, use [Keep a Changelog](https://keepachangelog.com/) at repo root, newest first.
- **Vite `define` / build-time version strings** (e.g. for a footer): only add when the UI or logic actually needs them â€” this template does not inject `__APP_VERSION__` by default.

## Communication

- Be direct and concise.
- If requirements are ambiguous, ask before large refactors.
- Briefly note non-obvious choices in responses or commits.
